# Styling Guide

This application uses Tailwind CSS for styling components.

## Core Styling Principles

- Use Tailwind utility classes for all styling
- Follow a consistent color scheme throughout the UI
- Ensure responsive design for all components
- Maintain accessibility standards

## Key Style Elements

- Chat interface styled for readability
- Message bubbles with distinct colors for user/assistant
- Clean, minimal UI with focus on content
- Dark mode support

## CSS Structure

- [app/globals.css](mdc:lite-llm-chatbot/app/globals.css) - Global styles and Tailwind imports
- Component-specific styles added directly via Tailwind classes
- Tailwind config can be extended in [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:lite-llm-chatbot/tailwind.config.ts)

## Styling Best Practices

When adding new components:
1. Use existing color scheme and spacing patterns
2. Leverage Tailwind's responsive utilities for mobile compatibility
3. Consider dark mode appearance with appropriate contrast
4. Group related Tailwind classes logically in your JSX
5. Use class extraction for repeated patterns
